As the internal functions became more complex, sympathetic neurones became aggregated in the dorsal region of the abdominal and of the pelvic cavity. These ganglionic aggregates which finally gave rise to the prevertebral sympathetic plexuses (fig. 4,p.s.) afforded a second link in the viscero-motor apparatus

