mesentery along the dorsal surface of the rectum (fig. 6, 9.r.). This ganglion so enormously developed in birds has no counterpart in any of the other classes of vertebrates. As will be shown presently, however, its prototype is, doubtless, represented in the aggregates of sympathetic cells which are associated with the rectum in embryos of the turtle.
